talking to Kaidou.

239
00:08:39,166 --> 00:08:41,750
♪

240
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:43,541
Ha, ha.
[screams]

241
00:08:43,625 --> 00:08:46,375
[SAIKI] There are some lines
you just don't cross, Kaidou.

242
00:08:46,458 --> 00:08:49,708
[TERUHASHI] This stinks.
What idiot ran around the school

243
00:08:49,791 --> 00:08:51,750
telling everyone
I brought chocolates?

244
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:53,333
Thanks to him, all day,
it's been like:

245
00:08:53,416 --> 00:08:55,041
That bag looks heavy.
Want me to carry it ?

246
00:08:55,125 --> 00:08:56,833
Are you thirsty?
I-I bought you a peach tea.

247
00:08:56,916 --> 00:08:58,875
Are you hungry? I brought you
every kind of snack.

248
00:08:58,958 --> 00:08:59,958
[TERUHASHI]
Enough!

249
00:09:00,041 --> 00:09:01,208
[boys chattering]

250
00:09:01,291 --> 00:09:02,666
[TERUHASHI]
Where did you come from?

251
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,166
You must be tired of walking.
Hop on!

252
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:05,666
[TERUASHI]
I'm tired of you people!

253
00:09:05,750 --> 00:09:07,625
Just leave me alone already!

254
00:09:07,708 --> 00:09:09,583
I need to use
the ladies' room, so bye!

255
00:09:09,666 --> 00:09:11,041
Wait!
I have a portable toilet.

256
00:09:11,125 --> 00:09:13,041
[TERUHASHI] Ugh, to hell
with Valentine's Day!

257
00:09:13,125 --> 00:09:14,666
They say I've got chocolates?

258
00:09:14,750 --> 00:09:17,708
Hmph! So, what if I do?
I'll just give this to Saiki.

259
00:09:17,791 --> 00:09:20,291
Obviously these are
gratitude chocolates,

260
00:09:20,375 --> 00:09:22,083
'cause I had dinner
at his house.

261
00:09:22,166 --> 00:09:23,708
So they're for him
and his parents.

262
00:09:23,791 --> 00:09:26,000
But these are the only
chocolates I brought today.

263
00:09:26,083 --> 00:09:29,083
If those guys out there find out
I gave them to Saiki,

264
00:09:29,166 --> 00:09:30,916
they'll tear him apart!

265
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:34,041
No, worse than that.
World War III will break out.

266
00:09:34,125 --> 00:09:36,375
It turns out my chocolates
are the most dangerous weapon

267
00:09:36,458 --> 00:09:39,291
in the history of mankind.
I can't give this to him.

268
00:09:39,375 --> 00:09:40,791
♪

269
00:09:40,875 --> 00:09:43,250
I'm sorry, Saiki.

270
00:09:45,166 --> 00:09:47,708
[SAIKI]
That's a little dramatic.

271
00:09:47,791 --> 00:09:51,958
♪ Saiki Kazan! Ah! ♪

272
00:09:52,041 --> 00:09:53,916
♪

273
00:09:57,208 --> 00:09:59,625
[NENDOU] Hey, buddy!
Let's hang out!

274
00:09:59,708 --> 00:10:01,333
Hey, you there, pal?

275
00:10:01,416 --> 00:10:04,208
[SAIKI] Oh, man.
Luckily my parents are out.

276
00:10:04,291 --> 00:10:06,000
Makes it easier to pretend
I'm not home.

277
00:10:06,083 --> 00:10:08,875
Come on, I dug a super big hole
in the vacant lot over there!

278
00:10:08,958 --> 00:10:10,916
[SAIKI] I can't think of
a less interesting thing

279
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,500
that's happened
in the past century.

280
00:10:12,583 --> 00:10:13,958
Dang, guess he's not home.

281
00:10:14,041 --> 00:10:15,541
[SAIKI] Finally,
some peace and quiet.

282
00:10:15,625 --> 00:10:16,916
He almost ruined
my Sunday.

283
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,500
Now I can get back
to that book I was re--

284
00:10:18,583 --> 00:10:20,083
Uh.
[crash]

285
00:10:20,166 --> 00:10:22,750
[SAIKI] Huh?
Nendou?

286
00:10:22,833 --> 00:10:24,083
How'd he get up here?

287
00:10:24,166 --> 00:10:25,625
--your face.
You look so scared.

288
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:27,541
Back up, kid,
this is harder than it looks.

289
00:10:27,625 --> 00:10:30,375
[SAIKI] Oh, it's not Nendou.
It's other Nendou.

290
00:10:30,458 --> 00:10:32,458
You can totally see me
right now, can't you?

291
00:10:32,541 --> 00:10:33,875
[SAIKI] I have so many
questions,

292
00:10:33,958 --> 00:10:36,208
but all I can say is:
go home!

293
00:10:36,291 --> 00:10:38,041
[SAIKI]
This is Nendou's father.

294
00:10:38,125 --> 00:10:40,041
He died 17 years ago,
and now he's a ghost.

295
00:10:40,125 --> 00:10:42,500
I've seen him twice before.

296
00:10:42,583 --> 00:10:44,666
First, when we
visited his grave.

297
00:10:44,750 --> 00:10:47,666
And then again through the eyes
of that medium Toritsuka.

298
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:49,791
Normally, seing ghosts
isn't one of my powers.

299
00:10:49,875 --> 00:10:51,541
Not sure why
I'm seeing one now,

300
00:10:51,625 --> 00:10:53,333
but nothing surprises
me anymore.

301
00:10:53,416 --> 00:10:56,333
As you can tell from his face
and annoying personality,

302
00:10:56,416 --> 00:10:57,875
he and his son share
a lot of DNA.

303
00:10:57,958 --> 00:10:59,500
[NENDOU'S DAD]
Huh? Huh?

304
00:10:59,583 --> 00:11:01,375
[SAIKI] Which is why
I want nothing to do with him.

305
00:11:01,458 --> 00:11:04,625
Hey, can you hear me? Hey, how
about now? How about now?

306
00:11:04,708 --> 00:11:07,208
Can you hear me now?
I can see inside your mind.

307
00:11:07,291 --> 00:11:08,875
[SAIKI]
Okay, this means war.

308
00:11:08,958 --> 00:11:10,541
Ah! So you can
hear me after all.

309
00:11:10,625 --> 00:11:12,625
Hey, I hear you do all
kinds of cool magic tricks.

310
00:11:12,708 --> 00:11:14,250
That's what Reita said.

311
00:11:14,333 --> 00:11:16,958
Man, I just love magic tricks.
Do one for me! Hey!

312
00:11:17,041 --> 00:11:18,916
Come on. Right now.
Will you do a trick?

313
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:21,500
[SAIKI] Great,
physical attacks don't work.

314
00:11:21,583 --> 00:11:23,375
I'm running
low on options here.

315
00:11:23,458 --> 00:11:25,500
Hey, now, come on,
quit ignoring me, you jerk!

316
00:11:25,583 --> 00:11:27,208
[SAIKI]
He really is just like Nendou.

317
00:11:27,291 --> 00:11:29,500
How long before he decides
he wants to call me "buddy"?

318
00:11:29,583 --> 00:11:30,875
Are you mocking me?

319
00:11:30,958 --> 00:11:32,416
[SAIKI]
You're literally in my face.

320
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:34,083
Come on,
say something to me!

321
00:11:34,166 --> 00:11:37,375
See? Was that so hard?
Now show me a trick, buddy.

322
00:11:37,458 --> 00:11:39,250
[SAIKI]
I've had enough.

323
00:11:39,333 --> 00:11:41,583
Seriously. Go see your son.

324
00:11:41,666 --> 00:11:43,583
Even though I guess
you never really knew him.

325
00:11:43,666 --> 00:11:45,583
That was awesome.
You just vanished.

326
00:11:45,666 --> 00:11:47,541
[SAIKI]
What the hell?

327
00:11:47,625 --> 00:11:49,375
[NEDOU'S DAD]
You got here in no time!

328
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:50,875
[SAIKI]
Am I stuck with this guy now?

329
00:11:50,958 --> 00:11:52,333
[NENDOU'S DAD]
Ooh, do another!

330
00:11:52,416 --> 00:11:54,000
[SAIKI] Sorry,
but you leave me no choice.

331
00:11:54,083 --> 00:11:55,041
Huh?

332
00:11:55,125 --> 00:11:56,541
[electricity buzzing]

333
00:11:56,625 --> 00:11:58,791
[NENDOU'S DAD]
Wow!

334
00:11:58,875 --> 00:12:00,666
[Saiki yelling]

335
00:12:00,750 --> 00:12:02,541
[Nendou's Dad yelling]

336
00:12:02,625 --> 00:12:04,000
[SAIKI]
Did it work?

337
00:12:04,083 --> 00:12:05,541
[NENDOU'S DAD]
That was pretty good.

338
00:12:05,625 --> 00:12:07,541
[SAIKI] Not a scratch.
And his regeneration

339
00:12:07,625 --> 00:12:09,208
is incredibly disturbing.

340
00:12:09,291 --> 00:12:10,583
[NENDOU'S DAD]
Hey, I like you!

341
00:12:10,666 --> 00:12:11,958
[SAIKI]
He's worse than Nendou!

342
00:12:12,041 --> 00:12:13,416
[NENDOU'S DAD]
Oh, hey, buddy!

343
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:15,291
[SAIKI] Could this guy
be my greatest foe?

344
00:12:15,375 --> 00:12:19,000
I guess it's come to this.
Gotta ask the medium for help.

345
00:12:19,083 --> 00:12:21,375
[TORITSUKA] Hm. Think this
one's the winner.

346
00:12:21,458 --> 00:12:23,583
[SAIKI] Is this what
you do at the temple all day?

347
00:12:23,666 --> 00:12:25,250
Saiki? Not cool!
Hey.

348
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:27,083
[TORITSUKA] Don't sneak
up on a guy when he's

349
00:12:27,166 --> 00:12:28,791
in the middle of a pin-up
mag tournament!

350
00:12:28,875 --> 00:12:30,833
[SAIKI] You say that like
it's a normal thing.

351
00:12:30,916 --> 00:12:33,416
[TORITSUKA] It's the losers'
semifinals, it'll be over soon.

352
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:34,958
[SAIKI] Who cares?
[screams]

353
00:12:35,041 --> 00:12:37,000
[SAIKI] This guy's
your guardian spirit, right?

354
00:12:37,083 --> 00:12:38,541
Wait, you can see him?

355
00:12:38,625 --> 00:12:41,333
You're a medium now too?
But that's my thing!

356
00:12:41,416 --> 00:12:42,958
You stole my thing,
you bastard!

357
00:12:43,041 --> 00:12:45,791
--[SAIKI] Not my problem.
--[TORITSUKA] You power hoarder!

358
00:12:45,875 --> 00:12:48,458
[SAIKI] Can you do something?
He won't leave me alone.

359
00:12:48,541 --> 00:12:51,333
[NENDOU'S DAD] Hey, Reita,
you were right about this guy.

360
00:12:51,416 --> 00:12:53,333
Hey, dude, you gotta leave
him alone, all right?

361
00:12:53,416 --> 00:12:54,916
[NENDOU'S DAD] I'm spending
every day with him!

362
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,416
[SAIKI] You're making
my life hell.

363
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:57,750
If you can't get him
to back off,

364
00:12:57,833 --> 00:12:59,208
what makes you think
I can? Huh?

365
00:12:59,291 --> 00:13:01,208
[SAIKI] Then there's
only one option left.

366
00:13:01,291 --> 00:13:03,916
[SAIKI] Why don't we see what'll
happen to your guardian spirit

367
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,583
after I kill you?
[TORITSUKA] What? No!

368
00:13:05,666 --> 00:13:06,833
Even if I die,
he won't go away!

369
00:13:06,916 --> 00:13:08,291
Besides,
I'm gonna haunt you, too!

370
00:13:08,375 --> 00:13:09,833
[SAIKI] Really?
I assume your soul

371
00:13:09,916 --> 00:13:11,750
doesn't have enough
substance to stick around.

372
00:13:11,833 --> 00:13:13,041
I really can't do anything!

373
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:14,625
Only spirits can
interact with others!

374
00:13:14,708 --> 00:13:17,666
[SAIKI] Of course!
Why didn't I think of that?

375
00:13:17,750 --> 00:13:21,708
Saiki? Hey!
Ah! Oh, no, Saiki's dead!

376
00:13:21,791 --> 00:13:23,250
[SAIKI] I'm using
a power that lets me

377
00:13:23,333 --> 00:13:24,833
separate my soul from my body.

378
00:13:24,916 --> 00:13:26,875
See, souls and spirits
are pretty similar.

379
00:13:26,958 --> 00:13:30,000
Oh. Astral projection. Okay.
[SAIKI] Be careful with that.

380
00:13:30,083 --> 00:13:32,000
Hey, I wanna see some more
magic tricks, buddy.

381
00:13:32,083 --> 00:13:34,333
[SAIKI] All right, boys
and girls. Here's a question.

382
00:13:34,416 --> 00:13:36,458
So, now I'm ghost
and he's a ghost.

383
00:13:36,541 --> 00:13:37,875
Whoa. I can touch you now.

384
00:13:37,958 --> 00:13:39,750
[SAIKI] Do you know what
happens in a certain

385
00:13:39,833 --> 00:13:42,500
mega-popular video game, when a
ghost-type fights a ghost-type?

386
00:13:42,583 --> 00:13:44,125
What's going on here?

387
00:13:44,208 --> 00:13:46,333
[SAIKI] The answer is:
it's super effective.

388
00:13:46,416 --> 00:13:48,500
[SAIKI] Man, the whole Nendou
family's a drag.

389
00:13:48,583 --> 00:13:50,541
Guess I'll head home
and get back to reading--

390
00:13:50,625 --> 00:13:53,791
Revenge time! This is for
messing with my porno mag girls!

391
00:13:53,875 --> 00:13:55,750
[both gasp]
[soft thud]

392
00:13:57,041 --> 00:13:58,916
♪

393
00:14:02,041 --> 00:14:04,458
[BUSUJIMA]
Today is your lucky day, ma'am!

394
00:14:04,541 --> 00:14:06,541
This is a rarity
known as "Golden Water."

395
00:14:06,625 --> 00:14:08,041
[super-fast speech]

396
00:14:08,125 --> 00:14:09,708
[KURUMI]
Wow, that sounds amazing!

397
00:14:09,791 --> 00:14:11,291
[BUSUJIMA]
And it's only 4500 yen a bottle!

398
00:14:11,375 --> 00:14:13,375
Really? I'll take it!
[BUSUJIMA] Thanks!

399
00:14:13,458 --> 00:14:15,333
What is all this?

400
00:14:15,416 --> 00:14:17,166
Welcome home, Ku!
Here, drink this!

401
00:14:17,250 --> 00:14:18,416
It's Golden Water!

402
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:19,666
[SAIKI]
She got tricked into buying

403
00:14:19,750 --> 00:14:20,958
a bunch of weird crap again?

404
00:14:21,041 --> 00:14:22,250
My mom never doubts anyone.

405
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:23,625
Got a space stone
bracelet, too!

406
00:14:23,708 --> 00:14:25,000
[SAIKI]
As you can see,

407
00:14:25,083 --> 00:14:26,583
she's an easy mark
for shady salesmen.

408
00:14:26,666 --> 00:14:28,416
Just look at all those
vacuum cleaners.

409
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:30,041
Now what's the deal
with this?

410
00:14:30,125 --> 00:14:32,250
Water from Mount Fuji?
With special healing powers?

411
00:14:32,333 --> 00:14:34,208
Clearly that's a lie.
Even if it was true,

412
00:14:34,291 --> 00:14:36,208
I could go and get it
for free any time.

413
00:14:36,291 --> 00:14:37,833
[KURUMI]
Now, drink up! The guy said

414
00:14:37,916 --> 00:14:40,000
that you'll never get
a cold or injury again.

415
00:14:40,083 --> 00:14:41,833
[SAIKI] Have you ever seen me
sick or injured?

416
00:14:41,916 --> 00:14:44,500
Look at the other
stuff I bought! Extinguishers!

417
00:14:44,583 --> 00:14:46,083
[SAIKI] I put fires out.
Don't need it.

418
00:14:46,166 --> 00:14:47,541
[KURUMI]
A pruning pole!

419
00:14:47,625 --> 00:14:49,083
[SAIKI] I can reach high places.
Don't need it.

420
00:14:49,166 --> 00:14:50,375
[KURUMI]
A levitation book!

421
00:14:50,458 --> 00:14:52,125
[SAIKI]
I can levitate. Don't need it.

422
00:14:52,208 --> 00:14:54,916
Egg cracking machine! Just set
the egg, press the handle

423
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:56,083
and the egg cracks!

424
00:14:56,166 --> 00:14:57,583
No one needs that.
[rings]

425
00:14:57,666 --> 00:14:59,458
Oh? Who could that be?

426
00:14:59,541 --> 00:15:02,458
Hello? What? You were arrested
for groping women?

427
00:15:02,541 --> 00:15:04,583
They'll release you
if we pay a million yen?

428
00:15:04,666 --> 00:15:06,541
I'll go wire the money!
This is terrible!

429
00:15:06,625 --> 00:15:07,916
Your dad's been--
Yeah, let's

430
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,250
get to the bank.
Hi! I'm home!

431
00:15:09,333 --> 00:15:10,791
[KURUMI]
What are you doing here?

432
00:15:10,875 --> 00:15:12,458
[SAIKI]
We thought you'd be in a jail.

433
00:15:12,541 --> 00:15:14,625
I didn't do it!
I don't go groping women!

434
00:15:14,708 --> 00:15:17,208
But the man on the phone
kept saying, "It's me!"

435
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:19,458
You fell for the classic
"It's me" scam!

436
00:15:19,541 --> 00:15:20,958
How'd you get fooled,
Kusuo?

437
00:15:21,041 --> 00:15:22,708
[SAIKI] It sounded
like something you'd do.

438
00:15:22,791 --> 00:15:25,166
It doesn't. I don't know
how you could fall for that.

439
00:15:25,250 --> 00:15:27,083
I can't believe
we almost lost a million yen!

440
00:15:27,166 --> 00:15:29,125
I see someone got you
to buy a bunch of crap.

441
00:15:29,208 --> 00:15:30,333
How much was all this?

442
00:15:30,416 --> 00:15:31,791
[KURUMI]
About a million yen.

443
00:15:31,875 --> 00:15:33,500
It's the same--
I gotta lick 75 shoes

444
00:15:33,583 --> 00:15:34,916
to make back
what you spent!

445
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,333
[SAIKI] Do you have
a yen-per-shoe rate?

446
00:15:36,416 --> 00:15:37,666
[KURUMI]
I'm so sorry.

447
00:15:37,750 --> 00:15:39,166
I bought all this
because I thought

448
00:15:39,250 --> 00:15:40,500
it would make you two
happy.

449
00:15:40,583 --> 00:15:42,250
You have nothing
to apologize for.

450
00:15:42,333 --> 00:15:44,541
You did it out of love
and that's what matters.

451
00:15:44,625 --> 00:15:47,083
Knowing that makes me happy.
Who cares about the money

452
00:15:47,166 --> 00:15:48,791
or the number of shoes
I have to lick.

453
00:15:48,875 --> 00:15:50,166
Oh, honey.
Forget about it.

454
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:51,375
Let's have dinner.
Aw!

455
00:15:51,458 --> 00:15:52,541
I'll get ready!

456
00:15:52,625 --> 00:15:54,166
Kusuo, please fix
this mess!

457
00:15:54,250 --> 00:15:55,541
[SAIKI]
Now you're panicking?

458
00:15:55,625 --> 00:15:57,583
These are still
in the return period.

459
00:15:57,666 --> 00:15:59,333
That was too easy.

460
00:15:59,416 --> 00:16:01,375
[laughs then screams]
Hey!

461
00:16:01,458 --> 00:16:03,375
[SAIKI] It's convenient
that I can apport things.

462
00:16:03,458 --> 00:16:05,625
All right! You got
my shoe-licking money back!

463
00:16:05,708 --> 00:16:08,000
Just for that, I'm gonna
buy you one coffee jelly!

464
00:16:08,083 --> 00:16:09,375
One?
As many as you want!

465
00:16:09,458 --> 00:16:10,791
I really am sorry.
Honey,

466
00:16:10,875 --> 00:16:12,166
I told you, it's okay.

467
00:16:12,250 --> 00:16:13,791
But the salesmen come by
all the time.

468
00:16:13,875 --> 00:16:15,375
Just today,
there must have been 10.

469
00:16:15,458 --> 00:16:16,958
Wow, that many?

470
00:16:17,041 --> 00:16:18,666
[SAIKI] We're probably
on a list of easy targets.

471
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:21,375
That's it! I'll get rid of
those vultures once and for all!

472
00:16:21,458 --> 00:16:22,541
[SAIKI]
Sudden headache.

473
00:16:22,625 --> 00:16:24,208
Don't want what you're
selling!

474
00:16:24,291 --> 00:16:26,375
[BUSUJIMA] You must be
the man of the house--

475
00:16:26,458 --> 00:16:27,666
My, do you think so?

476
00:16:27,750 --> 00:16:29,041
[BUSUJIMA]
I have just the thing--

477
00:16:29,125 --> 00:16:30,625
We'll take three!
Make that seven!

478
00:16:30,708 --> 00:16:31,875
[SAIKI]
That won't work.

479
00:16:31,958 --> 00:16:33,500
I just saw you failing
miserably.

480
00:16:33,583 --> 00:16:35,916
Then why don't you go
destroy all those companies?

481
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:38,208
[SAIKI] No, we need to show
that our resolve is so strong

482
00:16:38,291 --> 00:16:40,500
that they'll remove us
from their sucker list.

483
00:16:40,583 --> 00:16:42,500
Which will only work
if it comes from Mom.

484
00:16:42,583 --> 00:16:44,833
Though, of course,
I'll give her a little help.

485
00:16:44,916 --> 00:16:46,250
[doorbell rings]

486
00:16:46,333 --> 00:16:48,083
Hello again, ma'am!
So good to see you.

487
00:16:48,166 --> 00:16:50,666
De'Seeve Healthy Foods
thanks you for your business!

488
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:52,541
Please,
just leave us alone!

489
00:16:52,625 --> 00:16:54,375
What? Wait!
Please leave!

490
00:16:54,458 --> 00:16:56,250
[BUSUJIMA] Let me guess.
Your husband got upset.

491
00:16:56,333 --> 00:16:58,000
I thought that
might be the case.

492
00:16:58,083 --> 00:17:00,666
Men tend to complain because
they have to work every day

493
00:17:00,750 --> 00:17:03,291
and the stress takes its toll.
Only you can save him!

494
00:17:03,375 --> 00:17:05,583
You have to look out
for your family's health!

495
00:17:05,666 --> 00:17:07,000
Give me everything
you have!

496
00:17:07,083 --> 00:17:08,458
[SAIKI] Oh, you're
so gullible, Mom.

497
00:17:08,541 --> 00:17:10,166
She's concerned
about our health.

498
00:17:10,250 --> 00:17:11,833
[SAIKI]
Enough of that. Switch on!

499
00:17:11,916 --> 00:17:13,916
[BUSUJIMA] Heh, heh! This
broad'll believe anything.

500
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,166
Huh?
She has no clue

501
00:17:15,250 --> 00:17:16,916
that she's just buying
tap water.

502
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,875
I'm gonna get
stinkin' rich off you!

503
00:17:18,958 --> 00:17:20,291
[KURUMI]
What's going on?

504
00:17:20,375 --> 00:17:22,125
[SAIKI] You guessed it.
Forced telepathy.

505
00:17:22,208 --> 00:17:24,750
I'm broadcasting
this slimy huckster's thoughts

506
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:26,541
directly into my mom's head.

507
00:17:26,625 --> 00:17:29,125
[BUSUJIMA] You're gonna drive
your family into bankruptcy.

508
00:17:29,208 --> 00:17:30,750
I'll be on
my way now-- Ahh!

509
00:17:30,833 --> 00:17:33,083
[scary voice]
Hold it, you son of a bitch.

510
00:17:33,166 --> 00:17:35,083
[Busujima screams then pants]

511
00:17:35,166 --> 00:17:36,583
So that's your plan?
Aah!

512
00:17:36,666 --> 00:17:38,375
[KURUMI] Drive my family
into bankruptcy?

513
00:17:38,458 --> 00:17:39,750
How dare you
try to get rich

514
00:17:39,833 --> 00:17:41,625
off my beloved family's
suffering!

515
00:17:41,708 --> 00:17:43,208
Actually,
before you leave,

516
00:17:43,291 --> 00:17:46,000
there is one more thing
I want from you. Your head!

517
00:17:46,083 --> 00:17:47,625
Get back here!
Help me!

518
00:17:47,708 --> 00:17:48,666
Aaarggh!

519
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:50,083
[SAIKI]
Something tells me

520
00:17:50,166 --> 00:17:51,333
he won't show up again.

521
00:17:51,416 --> 00:17:52,750
Hm? It's a ring.

522
00:17:52,833 --> 00:17:54,291
We should return this,
too, before--

523
00:17:54,375 --> 00:17:56,791
Hmph!
Whew, that was scary.

524
00:17:56,875 --> 00:17:58,916
[SAIKI] Is this--
What's causing it?

525
00:18:00,041 --> 00:18:02,000
My telepathy's gone.

526
00:18:02,083 --> 00:18:04,208
[man singing in Japanese]

527
00:18:07,583 --> 00:18:09,458
♪

528
00:18:12,083 --> 00:18:15,166
[SAIKI] After looking into it,
turns out this is a normal ring.

529
00:18:15,250 --> 00:18:17,791
But it's made of something
called "germanium,"

530
00:18:17,875 --> 00:18:19,833
and I think that's what's
doing it.

531
00:18:19,916 --> 00:18:21,625
I don't know exactly how
it works,

532
00:18:21,708 --> 00:18:23,583
but it seems like
I can't use telepathy

533
00:18:23,666 --> 00:18:25,708
when my skin is touching
this material.

534
00:18:25,791 --> 00:18:28,166
What a pleasant surprise
I've stumbled upon!

535
00:18:29,291 --> 00:18:31,166
It's so quiet.

536
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:33,958
Thanks to the telepathy I've
been cursed with since birth,

537
00:18:34,041 --> 00:18:36,416
I hear the thoughts of anyone
within a 200 meter radius.

538
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:38,875
That means that even in
a residential area like this,

539
00:18:38,958 --> 00:18:41,916
I'm constantly bombarded with
mall food court levels of noise.

540
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:43,541
But right now,
all I hear is silence.

541
00:18:43,625 --> 00:18:44,958
[chuckles]
I did it!

542
00:18:45,041 --> 00:18:46,458
[KUNIHARU] What are you
still doing here?

543
00:18:46,541 --> 00:18:48,208
Are you pretending
to be startled?

544
00:18:48,291 --> 00:18:50,291
Food's on the table.
You read my mind, right?

545
00:18:50,375 --> 00:18:51,708
[SAIKI] Not used to being
snuck-up on.

546
00:18:51,791 --> 00:18:53,416
It's nice that all
the noise is gone,

547
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:55,791
but surprises like that
can't be good for my heart.

548
00:18:55,875 --> 00:18:58,041
When my telepathy's on,
I know when someone's coming

549
00:18:58,125 --> 00:18:59,375
before they get to me.

550
00:18:59,458 --> 00:19:01,166
[KUNIHARU]
Huh? Kusuo's not down yet?

551
00:19:01,250 --> 00:19:02,708
Food's gonna get cold.

552
00:19:02,791 --> 00:19:04,625
[SAIKI]
In fact, I even know the reason

553
00:19:04,708 --> 00:19:06,125
why they're coming
to see me.

554
00:19:06,208 --> 00:19:08,375
That's just been the norm
my entire life.

555
00:19:08,458 --> 00:19:10,000
But now,
while I have this ring,

556
00:19:10,083 --> 00:19:12,208
it's like having millions
of unpredictable

557
00:19:12,291 --> 00:19:14,416
Nendous walking around,
which is terrifying.

558
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:15,833
I should take it off.

559
00:19:15,916 --> 00:19:18,208
No, it could still be useful.
Oh, right!

560
00:19:18,291 --> 00:19:20,250
There's somewhere
I always wanted to go

561
00:19:20,333 --> 00:19:21,625
if I ever lost my
telepathy.

562
00:19:21,708 --> 00:19:23,833
I'm here,
and I didn't even teleport.

563
00:19:23,916 --> 00:19:26,333
I had to deal with Nendous
B, C, and D along the way,

564
00:19:26,416 --> 00:19:27,958
but I cut those scenes
for time.

565
00:19:28,041 --> 00:19:29,833
Anyway, this is where
I wanted to go.

566
00:19:29,916 --> 00:19:31,458
A movie theater!

567
00:19:31,541 --> 00:19:34,083
Telepathy and movie theaters
are a bad combination.

568
00:19:34,166 --> 00:19:36,250
Back when I was a kid,
there was this movie

569
00:19:36,333 --> 00:19:39,083
I'd been looking forward to
for a long time, but then--

570
00:19:39,166 --> 00:19:41,041
[MAN 1] I can't believe
he was dead the whole time!

571
00:19:41,125 --> 00:19:42,250
[MAN 2]
What a crazy twist!

572
00:19:42,333 --> 00:19:43,625
[SAIKI]
I had the ending spoiled.

573
00:19:43,708 --> 00:19:45,416
At theaters,
there are two groups.

574
00:19:45,500 --> 00:19:47,833
Those who are about to watch,
and those who've just seen.

575
00:19:47,916 --> 00:19:51,083
So the next time, I went to the
very first show on opening day.

576
00:19:51,166 --> 00:19:53,166
[TICKET LADY] All right,
here you go. Enjoy the movie.

577
00:19:53,250 --> 00:19:55,291
I hope he can handle
that one.

578
00:19:55,375 --> 00:19:56,958
It's kind of scary
at the end

579
00:19:57,041 --> 00:19:58,958
when the main guy
turns to goo and dies.

580
00:19:59,041 --> 00:20:01,625
[SAIKI] An unexpected ambush.
But I decided to stick around

581
00:20:01,708 --> 00:20:03,750
and watch it anyway,
knowing how it ended.

582
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:05,166
[MAN]
This part's boring.

583
00:20:05,250 --> 00:20:06,875
[WOMAN]
What else was that guy in?

584
00:20:06,958 --> 00:20:09,166
[audience chatter overlapping]

585
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:11,708
[SAIKI] Since then, I've
given up on going to the movies.

586
00:20:11,791 --> 00:20:13,791
But now, I've got this!
Today's the day

587
00:20:13,875 --> 00:20:15,458
I make my triumphant return!

588
00:20:15,541 --> 00:20:17,166
[TICKET LADY]
Here you go. Enjoy the movie.

589
00:20:17,250 --> 00:20:19,500
[SAIKI] Hmph! That was easy
enough. Thanks, Nendou E.

590
00:20:19,583 --> 00:20:21,375
--[MAN 1] That was something.
--[MAN 2] Yeah.

591
00:20:21,458 --> 00:20:24,083
[SAIKI] Heh! Nice try,
Nendou F and Nendou G.

592
00:20:24,166 --> 00:20:25,708
You may have all ready seen
the movie,

593
00:20:25,791 --> 00:20:27,250
but you can't
spoil it for me.

594
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:29,250
[MAN 3]
I was in the bathroom! Wait up!

595
00:20:29,333 --> 00:20:30,750
Oh, no--
What'd you guys think

596
00:20:30,833 --> 00:20:32,750
when his bones got broken
and then he died?

597
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:34,416
[MAN 2]
Yeah, that was nuts!

598
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:36,583
[SAIKI] Just kidding.
Unlike with people's thoughts,

599
00:20:36,666 --> 00:20:38,875
just plug your ears
to block out their voices.

600
00:20:38,958 --> 00:20:40,375
[MAN 1]
The movie kind of sucked.

601
00:20:40,458 --> 00:20:41,875
[MAN 2]
Oh, yeah, it was awful.

602
00:20:41,958 --> 00:20:43,375
[GIRL]
The movie in Theater-3

603
00:20:43,458 --> 00:20:44,625
will begin shortly.

604
00:20:44,708 --> 00:20:46,541
[SAIKI]
Okay, I went overboard on food.

605
00:20:46,625 --> 00:20:48,583
But I've got a lot of time
to make up for.

606
00:20:48,666 --> 00:20:51,583
Hey! Watch where you're going
there, you jackass!

607
00:20:51,666 --> 00:20:53,333
Yeesh, it almost
spilled on me.

608
00:20:53,416 --> 00:20:54,916
[SAIKI]
Ugh! All that food, lost.

609
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,583
Stupid Nendous I and J.
Or should I say Idiot and Jerk?

610
00:20:57,666 --> 00:20:59,708
Never would've happened
with telepathy.

611
00:20:59,791 --> 00:21:01,333
No, what am I thinking?

612
00:21:01,416 --> 00:21:03,500
I'm happy to finally be rid
of that power!

613
00:21:03,583 --> 00:21:06,291
Nuisances like these are just
the price I have to pay!

614
00:21:06,375 --> 00:21:07,875
[thuds]
Ugh!

615
00:21:07,958 --> 00:21:10,166
[SAIKI] I should never rely
on supernatural powers!

616
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:12,791
Well, here's my seat.
Seems pretty comfortable.

617
00:21:12,875 --> 00:21:15,208
Heh, heh! I love you,
germanium ring.

618
00:21:15,291 --> 00:21:17,041
I'm never gonna take you off!

619
00:21:17,125 --> 00:21:19,125
[gasps]
Uh, Saiki?

620
00:21:19,208 --> 00:21:20,875
Wow, what
a coincidence!

621
00:21:20,958 --> 00:21:23,791
[SAIKI] Of all people,
I had to sit next to Teruhashi.

622
00:21:23,875 --> 00:21:26,333
--Mm...
--[SAIKI] She's acting weird.

623
00:21:26,416 --> 00:21:28,541
[SAIKI] I have no idea
what she's thinking!

624
00:21:28,625 --> 00:21:31,541
She's not Teruhashi,
she's Nendou L!

625
00:21:31,625 --> 00:21:33,125
This is bad,
but I can't worry about it now.

626
00:21:33,208 --> 00:21:35,500
I've been wanting
to see this movie for a while.

627
00:21:35,583 --> 00:21:37,958
The live-action
<i>Healthy Warrior! Specialiser!</i>

628
00:21:38,041 --> 00:21:40,708
I mean, a live-action
anime adaptation is pretty much

629
00:21:40,791 --> 00:21:43,000
a guaranteed fail,
but thanks to this ring--

630
00:21:43,083 --> 00:21:45,166
[TERUHASHI] Uh, Saiki. I'm
not just making up an excuse,

631
00:21:45,250 --> 00:21:47,083
but I don't want you to get
the wrong idea.

632
00:21:47,166 --> 00:21:49,083
I'm with someone, but--
Oh?

633
00:21:49,166 --> 00:21:51,166
[MUGAMI]
Hey, Kokomi, I got us popcorn!

634
00:21:51,250 --> 00:21:53,291
[SAIKI]
Who's that? If Teruhashi thinks

635
00:21:53,375 --> 00:21:54,916
he's worthy of her,
he must be--

636
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,916
Hey, you there!
Just what are you doing

637
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:58,416
with my Kokomi?
[SAIKI] Hm?

638
00:21:58,500 --> 00:22:00,166
Don't take
your sunglasses off!

639
00:22:00,250 --> 00:22:01,791
--[WOMAN] Oh, my god!
--[MAN 1] Look, it's him!

640
00:22:01,875 --> 00:22:03,750
[MAN 2] That's Toru Mugami!
The star of the movie!

641
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:05,708
--[GIRL] He's here?
--[audience clamoring]

642
00:22:05,791 --> 00:22:07,583
[SAIKI] I can't believe
she brought him here.

643
00:22:07,666 --> 00:22:09,666
You know,
this never would've happened

644
00:22:09,750 --> 00:22:11,416
if I'd been using telepathy.

645
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:15,125
♪

646
00:22:21,666 --> 00:22:23,666
[woman singing in Japanese]

647
00:23:42,291 --> 00:23:43,625
[SAIKI]
I helped all those

648
00:23:43,708 --> 00:23:45,583
pains-in-the-neck
again this episode.

649
00:23:45,666 --> 00:23:47,166
I don't know why
I keep doing that.

650
00:23:47,250 --> 00:23:50,875
But at least I discovered
the magic of germanium.

651
00:23:50,958 --> 00:23:53,083
Next time on
<i>The Disastrous Life of Saiki K,</i>

652
00:23:53,166 --> 00:23:54,875
I've got another
pain-in-the-neck

653
00:23:54,958 --> 00:23:56,000
to worry about now?

